The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable system for embedding items and projecting them into compatible prototypes, which can be used for item recommendation and generation. This involves learning a novel Projected Compatibility Distance (PCD) function that is differentiable and ensures diversity. The paper also uses a Metric-regularized Conditional Generative Adversarial Network (MrCGAN) to visualize the candidate compatible prototypes. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these are the most relevant areas for developing and evaluating the proposed system. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for processing textual descriptions of items, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the use of generative models for image generation and evaluation suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
